********************************************************************************
 cpx - create Pbox shape file (M)
********************************************************************************

     Syntax:  cpx                                                       
              cpx(ref_pw90, ref_pwr)                                    
              cpx('g') - for gradient shapes                            
              cpx('w') - for weighting function profiles                            

 Description: cpx calls the Pbox command (UNIX), which generates the specified 
              pulse shape or decoupling / spin locking pattern, as defined by 
              the file shapelib/Pbox.inp, see also man('Pbox'). 

   Arguments: ref_pw90 - reference 90 degree pulse width (in us) at ref_pwr. 
              ref_pwr  - reference power level (in dB steps). Required for 
                         B1 field calibration.
              The argument 'g' is required only when generating gradient shapes
              and if the file type is not specified otherwise.

    Examples: cpx
              cpx(pw90*compH,tpwr)
              cpx(70.5,35)
	      cpx('g')

     Related: dprofile - view pulse excitation profile from Pbox software (M)
	      dshape - display pulse shape pattern (M)
	      dshapei - display pulse shape interactively (M)
	      dshapef - display last generated pulse shape (M)
	      opx - open shape definition file for Pbox software (M)
	      Pbox - Pandora's box pulse/pattern generator (UNIX, M)
	      pprofile - plot pulse excitation profile from Pbox software (M)
	      pshape - plot pulse shape or modulation pattern (M)
	      pxcal - assign Pbox calibration data to the current experiment (M)
	      Pxspy - create shape definition using Fourier coefficients (UNIX)
	      shdec - set up shaped pulse / shaped decoupling experiment (M)
              setwave - add a wave to the Pbox.inp file
              putwave - add a wave to the Pbox.inp file
              pxshape - generate a single band Pbox shapefile
              pph - print pulse header
              pboxpar - add Pbox parameter to Pbox.inp file
              pboxget - extract calibration data from a Pbox shapefile
              pbox_dmf - extract dmf value from pbox.cal or Pbox shapefile
              pbox_dres - extract dres value from pbox.cal or Pbox shapefile
              pbox_name - extract the name of last shapefile generated by Pbox
              pbox_pw - extract pulse length value from pbox.cal or Pbox shapefile
              pbox_pwr - extract pulse power value from pbox.cal or Pbox shapefile
              pbox_pwrf - extract pulse fine power value from pbox.cal or Pbox 
                          shapefile
